responses.text:
O God! Thou art my God alone;
In darkest night, my heart doth call
To Thee, my guiding star, my throne;
My soul, a flame, that burns for all.
In solitude, I find my way
To Thee, my comfort, night and day;
The world, a wilderness, may seem
But in Thy presence, I am serene.
Thy voice, a whisper, in my ear
A gentle breeze, that calms my fear;
Thy love, a river, that doth flow
And in its depths, my spirit glows.
So let me walk, in Thy pure light
And follow Thee, through darkest night;
For Thou, O God, art my heart's home
And in Thy love, I am not alone.

O God! Thou art my God alone;
In darkness and in light, I call to Thee,
My heart, a flame that flickers, yet is thrown
Upon the altar of Thy majesty.

In times of joy, I lift my voice to Thee,
In sorrow, I pour out my soul's plea;
Thou art my rock, my shelter, and my sea,
The depths of which I long to explore and see.

Thy love, a river, flows through my darkest night,
And in its waters, I am made anew;
Thy presence, a warm breeze, that soothes my fright,
And in its gentle touch, I am made true.

O God! Thou art my God alone;
My every breath, a prayer, a plea, a song;
Forever and always, I will make Thee known,
My heart, a vessel, where Thy love will belong.

O God! Thou art my God alone;
In darkness, I search for thy throne.
My heart, a flame that burns with desire,
Yearning to be with thee, my one true fire.

In times of sorrow, I call thy name;
In joy, I praise thee, and thy love proclaim.
Thou art my refuge, my guiding light;
My soul, a vessel, filled with thy delight.

I'll follow thee, through life's plodding pace;
Through trials and tribulations, I'll find my place.
For thou, O God, art my heart's desire;
My love, my all, my one true fire.

So let me walk, in thy loving light;
And in thy presence, take my flight.
For thou, O God, art my God alone;
My heart, my soul, my everything, my own.

O God! Thou art my God alone;
In darkness, Thou art my shining light;
My heart beats for Thee, my soul is Thine own,
In Thee, I find my peace, my guiding sight.

Thy love is my solace, my comfort and my rest;
Thy voice is my whisper, that gently calms my breast;
Thou art my shelter, my refuge and my tower;
In Thee, I find my strength, my power.

I search for Thee, I seek Thy face;
My soul longs for Thee, in every time and place;
Thou art my everything, my all in all;
Without Thee, I am nothing, I would surely fall.

So I surrender, I give myself to Thee;
Take me, O God, and set my soul free;
I am Thine, forever and always;
O God! Thou art my God, my heart's sweet praise.
